description: description
This property references the Donor organism from which the BioSample was acquired.
A reference to the site within the organism from which the BioSample was taken.
A priori cell type(s) for the sample, a human assignment of cell type.
The type of biosample represented by the record.
A property that identifies a disease or condition has been reported in this entity.
The units (e.g. years or days) of the Age of the Donor at the point in time that the BioSample was obtained or other representative entity (test, diagnosis, treatment...) was created.
Lower bound for age of donor at time sample was taken. If any age at collection data is present, must specify a unit as well.
Upper bound for age of donor at time sample was taken. If any age at collection data is present, must specify a unit as well.

comments: For example: Homo sapiens from NCBITaxon or http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606
description: A reference to the organism type.
A reference to the BiologicalSex of the Donor organism. \"An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's physical expression of sexual characteristics. [PATO_0001894]\
A property that relects a Human Donor's reported ethnic origins.
A property that relects a HumanDonor's reported major contributing ancestral origins based on genetic/genomic data.
Data modality describes the biological nature of the information gathered as the result of an Activity, independent of the technology or methods used to produce the information.
The name of the file.
The fully qualified path to the file.

comments: The definition of this field follows the convention used by the Human Cell Atlas.
description: An indication of the format of an electronic file; include the full file extension including compression extensions.
Property that describes the approximate size of a file in megabytes.
md5 checksum for the file
A reference to the collection of sequences taken as the standard for a given organism. May be defined by https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/grc.
Contains information about the sample(s) included in the study.
Demographic and phenotypic information about the donor.
Information for files associated with the study.
